other_tests.findings: Blastomycosis, with broad-based budding yeast. Cultures grew Blastomyces dermatitidis.
A 2.0 x 1.9 x 3.1-cm hypoechoic irregular avascular area within the superior pole of the left kidney.
A 4.8 x 3.1 x 9.5-cm mass involving the left kidney, the psoas muscle, and the crus of the diaphragm; a 3.7 x 1.3 x 1.5-cm lytic lesion of the right ilium with ill-defined margins.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At follow-up, revealed healing of the lesion in the right ilium with a marked cortical response.

other_tests.procedure_name: MRI of the abdomen and pelvis
other_tests.findings: Multiple lytic lesions noted within the ischium, both femoral necks, and both ilia.
